4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp that allows individuals to become cybersecurity specialists without any prior knowledge. The program provides a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills for securing these environments. Participants will also learn cloud security, penetration testing (both offensive and defensive), cyber threat intelligence analysis, and data loss prevention strategies. The bootcamp is 16 weeks long, with 3 live online classes per week. Class size is limited to 16 people, and upon completion, participants receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate recognized by multiple institutions. No previous experience is required to enroll in the bootcamp. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560. For more information, visit https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. stop